## Overview

My research examines how American political institutions shape democratic governance, with particular focus on presidential power, electoral accountability, and the geographic dimensions of political behavior. Through empirical analysis combining survey experiments, administrative data, and formal modeling, I investigate when and why democratic institutions succeed or fail to represent citizen interests.

